Package GUI

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Error
    The Error class display an error message, with a given title and message.
    Launch
    This class is the core of the GUI, it contains all the listeners of the buttons of each panel.
    MenuBarCourier
    The class MenuBarCourier creates the menu bar displayed on the courier panel.
    MenuBarCustomer
    The class MenuBarCustomer creates the menu bar displayed on the customer panel.
    MenuBarManager
    The class MenuBarManager creates the menu bar displayed on the manager panel.
    MenuBarRestaurant
    The class MenuBarRestaurant creates the menu bar displayed on the restaurant panel.
    MessageInputText
    The MessageInputText class display a question message, with a given title and input message to display.
    MessageList
    The MessageList class display a question message, with a given title and message, and the list to display, containing the elements to choose.
    MessageMealOfTheWeek
    The MessageMealOfTheWeek class display a question message, with a given restaurant in which the meal of the week has to be chosen.
    MessagePay
    The MessagePay class display a question message, with a given double which represents the price of the order.
    MessageRemoveSomething
    The MessageRemoveSomething class display a question message, with a given order containing the lists of the chosen single items and meals.
    MessageRemoveSomethingFromMenu
    The MessageRemoveSomethingFromMenu class display a question message, with a given restaurant in which the menu has to be set, and a string representing the action to do.
    MessageSave
    The MessageSave class display a question message to ask if the user wants to save the account.
    MessageSetProfile
    The MessageSetProfile class display a question message, with a given contact (email, phone, adress) to set.
    MessageShowText
    The MessageShowText class display an information message, with a given message and title to display.
    PanelAddSingleItem
    The class PanelAddSingleItem creates the panel used to add a new single item to the menu, it is only visible by a restaurant.
    PanelChooseDate
    The class PanelChooseDate creates the panel used to choose the dates for computing the earnings, it is only visible by a restaurant.
    PanelCourier
    The class PanelCourier creates the panel visible by the couriers.
    PanelCreateMeal
    The class PanelCreateMeal creates the panel used to create a new meal and add it to the restaurant menu, it is only visible by a restaurant.
    PanelCreator
    The class PanelCreator is the second most important class of the GUI.
    PanelCustomer
    The class PanelCustomer creates the panel visible by the customers.
    PanelCustomerOrder
    The class PanelCustomerOrder creates the panel used to make an order, it is only visible by a customer.
    PanelFirstPage
    The class PanelFirstPage creates the first panel visible by everyone.
    PanelLogin
    The class PanelLogin creates the panel used to login, it is visible by everyone.
    PanelManager
    The class PanelManager creates the panel visible by the managers.
    PanelRegister
    The class PanelRegister creates the panel used to register to the myFoodora system, it is visible by everyone.
    PanelRegisterCourier
    The class PanelRegisterCourier creates the panel used to register as a new courier, it is visible by those who want to be courier.
    PanelRegisterCustomer
    The class PanelRegisterCustomer creates the panel used to register as a new customer, it is visible by those who want to be customer.
    PanelRegisterManager
    The class PanelRegisterManager creates the panel used to register as a new manager, it is visible by those who want to be manager.
    PanelRegisterRestaurant
    The class PanelRegisterRestaurant creates the panel used to register as a new restaurant, it is visible by those who want to be restaurant.
    PanelRestaurant
    The class PanelRestaurant creates the panel visible by the restaurants.
